@startuml
title Chinese Remainder Theorem - Ring Isomorphism (main concept)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "Z_mn world" {
  [x  (single residue mod mn)] as Zmn
}

package "Z_m x Z_n world" {
  [(a, b) = (x mod m, x mod n)] as Prod
  note bottom of Prod
    componentwise + and x
    inverses componentwise
  end note
}

Zmn -right-> Prod : forward (cheap)\nreduce mod m and mod n
Prod -left-> Zmn : reverse (CRT reconstruction)\nx = a (n^-1 mod m) n + b (m^-1 mod n) m  (mod mn)

note top of Zmn
  gcd(m, n) = 1  =>  Z_mn  isomorphic to  Z_m x Z_n
  bijective, preserves + and x
end note
@enduml
